\begin_layout Standard
In relation to both types of research, we have identified causality and
 omitted variables as remaining challenges.
 For questions of causality, exogenous variation is key.
 Such variations in most EQ exposures remain difficult to identify, but
 researchers could profitably remain on the look-out for them (for example,
 the abolition of the western extension of London's Congestion Charging
 zone, or the closure of Greenwich Park during the 2012 Olympics, might
 be investigated as possible candidates).
 In principle, spatial econometric models could help to mitigate omitted
 variables issues: to date only one application of these models to SWB and
 EQ is known, and none with high-resolution data
